&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a UK-based Database Administrator / Cloud Database Engineer to help support the next generation of cloud-based public safety software for UK police forces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will help ensure the stability, performance, security, and reliability of Mark43’s production database systems. You will work closely with engineering, infrastructure, security, delivery, and customer-facing teams to support highly available systems used by public safety agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, it is expected to independently own well-scoped database administration tasks, contribute to production reliability, support incident response, and collaborate effectively with senior engineers and DBAs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because this role may involve work with UK police customers, candidates must be eligible to obtain and maintain the required UK police and/or government security vetting, including NPPV3 and, where applicable, SC clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the administration, monitoring, and reliability of production database systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure MySQL databases are configured, maintained, backed up, and monitored appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, investigate, and help tune problematic queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in database performance analysis, capacity planning, and operational readiness reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support database-related incident response, including investigation, remediation, and follow-up actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with engineering teams to help improve database usage patterns, query performance, and schema design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to infrastructure-as-code workflows and automation for database operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain documentation, runbooks, operational procedures, and knowledge-sharing materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with security and compliance teams to support customer, regulatory, and vetting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with UK delivery and customer teams to support public safety deployments in a secure and reliable manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Need&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4 years of professional experience administering MySQL or similar relational databases in production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting cloud-hosted database systems, preferably AWS RDS, Aurora, or Azure database services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with database monitoring, alerting, backup, recovery, replication, and performance tuning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience troubleshooting database issues in production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working with infrastructure-as-code tools and automated operational workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A working understanding of cloud infrastructure, networking, security, and access controls.&lt;/li&gt;
