&lt;h3&gt;About This Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a UK-based Senior / Staff Database Administrator to help lead the design, reliability, security, and operational maturity of Mark43’s production database infrastructure for UK public safety customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will serve as a senior technical owner for database reliability and performance. You will partner with engineering, infrastructure, security, delivery, and customer teams to ensure that Mark43’s database systems are stable, scalable, secure, observable, and ready to support mission-critical public safety workloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, it is expected to independently own complex database initiatives and mentor others, provide technical direction, influence cross-team architecture, lead high-impact reliability programs, and serve as a trusted authority across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because this role may involve work with UK police customers, candidates must be eligible to obtain and maintain the required UK police and/or government security vetting, including NPPV3 and, where applicable, SC clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and improve the reliability, performance, security, and scalability of production database systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead database monitoring, alerting, capacity planning, backup, recovery, replication, and disaster recovery practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, diagnose, and resolve complex database performance and availability issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering teams on schema design, indexing strategies, query optimization, and safe database change management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical planning for database migrations, upgrades, scaling strategies, and operational improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve infrastructure-as-code, automation, observability, and repeatability across database operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain database runbooks, operational standards, and production readiness criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in and, when appropriate, lead database-related incident response, post-incident reviews, and remediation planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with security, compliance, and delivery teams to meet customer, regulatory, and vetting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical guidance and mentorship to engineers, DBAs, and operational teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent database reliability concerns in architecture reviews, roadmap planning, and customer-readiness discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build the operational foundation required to support UK police customers and future UK public safety partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
